    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - OPERATION - RELIEF VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>RELIEF VALVE</title>
        <para>Some TAS gears (with or without poppets) are supplied with a relief valve. The relief valve limits maximum
            supply pressure to protect the power steering gear, but it does not reduce pressure as the steered wheels
            approach the axle stops.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
